(Don't forget to drop by the SPARC booth - #673 - for an update on =20
our latest activities.)


SPARC-ACRL Forum at ALA Midwinter
AUTHORS & AUTHORITY: Perspectives on Negotiating Licenses and Copyright

A publisher, an attorney, and a librarian will provide insights into =20
the ways that the traditional relationship between author and =20
publisher is changing: from individual author's addenda included with =20=

publishing agreements to large-scale efforts from universities and =20
organizations like Creative Commons and Science Commons. This SPARC-=20
ACRL Forum will outline a path for the future that will better serve =20
academe and the public. SPARC will also introduce its new partnership =20=

with Science Commons and discuss ways that SPARC members and the =20
scholarly community can benefit from the new, online SPARC Author=92s =20=

Addendum.

Speakers include:

- David Hoole, Head of Brand Marketing and Content Licensing, Nature =20
Publishing Group

- Mike Carroll, Associate Professor of Law, Villanova University =20
School of Law and Board Member of Creative Commons

- John Ober, Director, Education and Strategy, California Digital =20
Library

Please join us for this event.
Reservations are not required.

Saturday, January 21, 4:00 - 6:00PM
Hilton Palacio del Rio, Salon Del Rey (Central & South)


